@page "/about"

<section class="about-hero">
    <h1>About Ripple</h1>
    <p>
        Ripple is a community‑driven aquaponics initiative working to reduce food insecurity in the 
        Chicagoland area. Our mission is simple: grow fresh, healthy food sustainably and make it 
        accessible to the communities that need it most.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="about-section">
    <h2>Our Story</h2>
    <p>
        Ripple began as a student‑led project rooted in research, sustainability, and community impact. 
        As we learned more about aquaponics — a closed‑loop system that grows fish and plants together — 
        we realized its potential to support neighborhoods facing food deserts.
    </p>
    <p>
        What started as an academic exploration has grown into a nonprofit effort dedicated to local 
        food production, education, and community empowerment.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="about-section">
    <h2>Our Mission</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Increase access to fresh, nutritious food</li>
        <li>Support local food pantries and distribution partners</li>
        <li>Provide hands‑on learning and volunteer opportunities</li>
        <li>Conduct research to improve aquaponics systems</li>
        <li>Build a scalable model that other communities can replicate</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section class="about-section">
    <h2>Why Chicagoland?</h2>
    <p>
        Chicago’s combination of harsh winters, rising food costs, and limited access to fresh produce 
        in many neighborhoods makes it an ideal place for year‑round aquaponics. Our facility is designed 
        to operate regardless of weather, ensuring consistent production and reliable distribution.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="about-section">
    <h2>Our Values</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Community</strong> — We work with, not just for, the neighborhoods we serve.</li>
        <li><strong>Sustainability</strong> — Our system conserves water, energy, and resources.</li>
        <li><strong>Education</strong> — We empower volunteers, students, and researchers.</li>
        <li><strong>Equity</strong> — Everyone deserves access to healthy food.</li>
        <li><strong>Innovation</strong> — We continually improve our systems through research.</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section class="about-section">
    <h2>Our Nonprofit Status</h2>
    <p>
        Ripple is in the process of registering as a <strong>501(c)(3)</strong> nonprofit organization 
        in Illinois. This status allows us to accept tax‑deductible donations, apply for grants, partner 
        with community organizations, and operate transparently and responsibly.
    </p>
</section>
